    • Method Detail

      • getGraph

        DirectedGraph<M,GraphEdge<M>> getGraph()
        In the graph a dependency relation is modeled by precursors direction That is, when sorted topologically, the most left element doesn't depend on anything. The foremost right element depends on it's precursors
        Returns:
        directed acyclic graph

      • getModules

        Set<M> getModules()
        Returns:
        a set of modules

      • getDirectDependencies

        Set<M> getDirectDependencies(M module)
        Parameters:
        module - The module having dependencies
        Returns:
        A set of direct dependencies of M, not considering transitive.

      • getAllDependencies

        Set<M> getAllDependencies(M module)
        Parameters:
        module - The module having dependencies
        Returns:
        A set of all dependencies of M, including transitive.

      • getTopologicalOrder

        List<M> getTopologicalOrder()
        Returns:
        a topologically sorted list of modules

      • getModuleRankings

        Map<M,Integer> getModuleRankings()
        Returns module ratings based on longest path algorithm and module priority. The modules sorted by the module rating descendingly are guaranteed to be in topological order.
        Returns:
        module rankings

      • walkGraph

        void walkGraph(ExecutorService executor,
               IConsumer<M> moduleConsumer)
        throws ExecutionException
        Note: The parallelism is determined automatically from ThreadPoolExecutor and processor cores. If this is not an option, use walkGraph(ExecutorService, IConsumer, int)
        Parameters:
        executor - an executor to be used for executing the closure
        moduleConsumer - a processing closure
        Throws:
        ExecutionException - when the closure throws an exception
